Structured automation outcome

This run is evaluating {{.Repository}} pull request #{{.PullRequestNumber}} ({{.PullRequestURL}}).

Before your final response, call `143-tools automation-run report` exactly once with:
- `decision`: `passed`, `changes_requested`, `advisory`, or `not_applicable`
- `reason`: one concise sentence explaining the decision
- `pull_request_title` and `head_sha` when known
- `external_action_type`, `external_action_url`, and `external_action_id` only when you actually created a GitHub review or comment

Decision meanings:
- `passed`: evaluated and no blocking change was requested
- `changes_requested`: you submitted a GitHub changes-requested review; the linked review URL is required
- `advisory`: you left non-blocking guidance, or found concerns that did not reject the PR
- `not_applicable`: the automation intentionally skipped this PR (for example draft, closed, or out of scope)

Do not infer the business decision from agent execution success. Do not use `REVIEW_CLEAN` or any internal pre-PR review-loop result as the outcome. Report only what this Main automation run decided and what external GitHub action it actually took.
